Ndagijimana told Parliament the economy was forecast to grow 6.2% in 2023 and around 7.5% in 2024 and 2025. The Finance Ministry estimates the economy grew 6.8% in 2022. He said overall spending for the 2022/23 fiscal year that runs from July to June would rise by just over 2% to $4.42 billion from the $4.32 billion announced in June, when he first presented the 2022/23 budget.
--Reuters--